l. 22. tertii generis. Reliefs do not fit into the classification of all payments as either ‘pene pecuniarie' or ‘sponte oblata! They differ from the latter, first, because the lord is bound to receive the homage and accept the relies of the tenant (Glanvill, IX. i. 1), and secondly, because the tenant would in most cases be in possession of the estate before relief became due, and the lord's remedy for neglect to pay relies is by distress (Glanvill, IX. viii. 4)
